GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 2
HOUSE BILL 4
Committee Substitute Favorable 4/1/25
Short Title: Sam's Law. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
January 30, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE TRAINING TO STUDENTS AND SCHOOL PERSONNEL ON
3 RECOGNIZING AND RESPONDING WHEN A PERSON IS EXPERIENCING A
4 SEIZURE.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1. This act shall be known as the "Seizure Safe Schools Act of 2025" or
7 "Sam's Law" and may be cited by those names.
8 SECTION 2. Article 25A of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended by
9 adding a new section to read:
10 "§ 115C-375.7. Seizure preparedness.
11 (a) Seizure Action Plan. – A written, individualized health plan developed between a
12 public school unit and the parent of a student enrolled in the public school unit who is diagnosed
13 with a seizure disorder. The Plan identifies the health care needs of the student and prepares
14 school personnel to meet those needs. The public school unit shall keep each Seizure Action Plan
15 on file in the office of a school administrator or school nurse employed by the unit and make the
16 Plan available to any school personnel and, with the permission of the student's parent, any
17 volunteer responsible for the supervision of the student. Each plan is valid for one school year.
18 (b) Seizure Action Plan Components. – The parent of a student diagnosed with a seizure
19 disorder may petition the public school unit for the development of a Seizure Action Plan. The
20 parent and school unit shall develop the Plan in accordance with the procedures developed by the
21 governing body of the public school unit. At a minimum, the Plan shall include the following
22 components:
23 (1) A written statement from the student's health care provider with all of the
24 following information:
25 a. The student's name.
26 b. Any seizure medication prescribed to the student.
27 c. The dosage and method of administering the seizure medication.
28 d. The frequency of administration of the seizure medication.
29 e. The symptoms necessitating administration of the seizure medication.
30 (2) A written statement from the parent indicating whether school personnel or
31 volunteers are permitted to administer seizure medication to the student. This
32 permission shall be renewed in each subsequent school year the student
33 attends a school in the public school unit.
34 (3) If school personnel or volunteers who meet the training requirements of this
35 section are authorized by the parent to administer seizure medication to a
36 student, the parent shall provide the school with at least one unopened dosage
*H4-v-2*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 of the medication with an intact pharmaceutical label. The school shall store
2 the medication in a safe and secure location accessible only by school
3 personnel or volunteers with training to administer seizure medication in
4 accordance with subsection (c) of this section.
5 (c) Employee Administration of Seizure Medication. – Each public school unit shall
6 ensure that at least one employee in each school in the unit is trained to administer or assist with
7 the self-administration of any seizure medication provided to the school pursuant to subsection
8 (b) of this section. The governing body of the public school unit shall adopt minimum training
9 requirements for these employees, which shall be consistent with training guidelines established
10 by the Epilepsy Foundation of America, Inc., or its successor. Any volunteer that supervises
11 students with seizure disorders may volunteer to attend the same training.
12 (d) Seizure Education Program. – The governing body of the public school unit shall
13 adopt a policy outlining the requirements of a seizure education program for all school personnel
14 having direct contact with students in grades kindergarten through 12. The seizure education
15 program shall be administered on an annual basis in each public school unit and, at a minimum,
16 shall provide education on the following topics:
17 (1) Instructions for administering seizure medications.
18 (2) Signs and symptoms of seizures and the appropriate steps to be taken to
19 respond to symptoms of a seizure.
20 (3) Any other guidelines established by the Epilepsy Foundation of America, Inc.,
21 or its successor.
22 (e) Self-Study Requirement. – The governing body of the public school unit shall adopt
23 a policy requiring all principals, school counselors, and teachers in the public school unit to
24 complete at least one hour of self-study review of seizure disorder materials each school year.
25 The governing body of the public school unit shall select the materials for study in accordance
26 with current practices and standards.
27 (f) Informational Poster. – The governing body of the public school unit shall ensure that
28 an informational display on seizure first aid is posted in at least one visible, high-traffic area in
29 each school in the public school unit."
30 SECTION 3.(a) G.S. 115C-12 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
31 "(50) Duty regarding seizures. – The State Board of Education shall adopt rules
32 regarding seizures in accordance with G.S. 115C-375.7 for all schools
33 operated under the control of the Board."
34 SECTION 3.(b) G.S. 115C-47 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
35 "(70) Duty regarding seizures. – Each local board of education shall adopt a policy
36 regarding seizures in accordance with G.S. 115C-375.7."
37 SECTION 3.(c) G.S. 115C-150.12C(15) is amended by adding a new
38 sub-subdivision to read:
39 "c. The board shall adopt a policy regarding seizures in accordance with
40 G.S. 115C-375.7."
41 SECTION 3.(d) G.S. 115C-218.75 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
42 "(p) Seizure Policy. – A charter school shall adopt a policy regarding seizures in
43 accordance with G.S. 115C-375.7."
44 SECTION 3.(e) G.S. 115C-238.66 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
45 "(23) Seizure policy. – A regional school shall adopt a policy regarding seizures in
46 accordance with G.S. 115C-375.7."
47 SECTION 3.(f) G.S. 116-11 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
48 "(12f) The Board of Governors shall adopt a policy regarding seizures in accordance
49 with G.S. 115C-375.7 for all school units, as defined in that section, operated
50 under the control of the Board of Governors."
Page 2 House Bill 4-Second Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 SECTION 4. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
2 Public Instruction the sum of fifty thousand dollars ($50,000) in nonrecurring funds to assist the
3 State Board of Education with the development of its seizure rules and with other costs associated
4 with the implementation of this act. The State Board of Education may share any materials or
5 rule language it develops pursuant to Section 3(a) of this act with the Board of Governors of The
6 University of North Carolina and the Division of Non-Public Education to facilitate the
7 development of other seizure policies that are consistent with this act.
8 SECTION 5. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies beginning with
9 the 2025-2026 school year.
